# Documentation Policy

Applies to every human-readable Markdown document.

## Bilingual Rule
- Every doc ships in two files: `name.md` (English) and `name.ko.md` (Korean).
- Keep both versions in sync. Update both in the same change.
- `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` are machine config and stay English-only.

## Style
- Use a terse, bullet-point style (개조식). Prefer fragments over long sentences.
- One page, one goal. Start with a short overview.
- No emojis.

## Technical Writing Checklist (technical-writing.dev)
- Structure
  - One goal per page; split if depth exceeds H4.
  - Lead with an overview; reader knows the takeaway up front.
  - Predictable, consistent headings and term usage.
  - Deliver value first; defer secondary detail.
  - Titles are concise, keyword-rich, declarative.
- Sentences
  - Keep only needed information; one idea per line.
  - Remove meta-discourse ("as mentioned above").
  - Be concrete; use action verbs.
  - Be consistent; expand acronyms on first use.
  - Make the subject clear; prefer active voice with the developer as subject.

